const articles = [
    {
        "articles": [
          {
            "name": "getting-started-with-react",
            "title": "The Basics of Building a React App",
            "content": [
              `React is a popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It allows developers to create dynamic, reusable components that can be easily composed into complex web applications.`,
              `To get started with React, you'll need to have a basic understanding of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. You'll also need to install Node.js and a package manager like npm or Yarn.`,
              `Once you have the tools you need, you can create a new React project using a tool like create-react-app. This will set up a basic project structure and provide you with a starting point for building your app.`
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "managing-state-in-react",
            "title": "How to Keep Track of Data in Your React App",
            "content": [
              `One of the most important aspects of building a React app is managing state. State refers to the data that is stored within a component and can change over time as the app is used.`,
              `To manage state in React, you'll typically use the useState hook or a state management library like Redux. These tools allow you to keep track of changes to your data and trigger updates to your UI as needed.`,
              `When managing state in React, it's important to think about how your data is structured and how it will be used throughout your app. You'll also need to consider how state changes will impact the performance and usability of your app.`
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "building-a-react-app-with-authentication",
            "title": "How to Add User Authentication to Your React App",
            "content": [
              `Adding user authentication to your React app can be a bit more complex than building a simple static app. However, it's an important feature that can help keep your app secure and improve the user experience.`,
              `To add authentication to your React app, you'll need to use a third-party authentication service like Auth0 or Firebase. These services provide easy-to-use APIs for handling user authentication and can help you add features like social login and password reset.`,
              `When building an authenticated React app, you'll also need to consider how to handle user data and protect sensitive information. You may need to implement additional security measures like encryption or tokenization to keep user data safe.`
            ]
          }
        ]
    }      
]
